In July and August 2004, devastating floods in Bangladesh claimed over 700 lives and submerged 38% of the country, displacing millions.
The military is conducting evacuations and relief efforts as major rivers overflow, affecting northern regions.
Monsoon rains and Himalayan snowmelt have marooned 200,000 people in the north.
The situation is expected to worsen as key rivers like the Ganges and Brahmaputra swell.
Over 100 deaths have been reported in India, Bangladesh, and Nepal, with millions displaced.
Efforts are underway to provide aid and support to those affected by the ongoing floods.
